er. Bake for 40-45 minutes (180°C) until sponge is cooked and a skewer inserted comes out clean."},{"content":"Allow to cool completely in tin, then transfer to a serving plate and dust with icing sugar. Cut into 16 pieces to serve."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Cover with aluminium foil halfway through baking if the cake is browning too much.<br>","Vanilla seeds can easily be removed from the vanilla pod; hold the pod at one end, slit with a sharp knife lengthwise, then scrape out the seeds with the tip of the knife.","The empty pod can still be used, it has lots of flavour. For example, you can make your own vanilla sugar, or cook the pod in milk for desserts.<br>","Instead of fresh pears, you can use tinned pear halves. Drain well then cut each pear half in half again, lengthwise."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h 20m","16 pieces"]}